<br>
Bunny sat on a chair, opposite the window, in the room. Feagins sat across from her and leaned forward.<br>
<br>
“You’ve been quiet. Penny for your thoughts.” She looked up at him, trying to hide the fear and apprehension in her eyes. She shrugged.<br>
<br>
“Just a lot of stuff I guess.” She paused and looked away from him. “Can you tell me why?” She asked in a quiet voice. He reached across and took her hands in his. She looked back at him.<br>
<br>
“Why I killed them or why I had to take you?” He asked in a sincere and gentle tone.<br>
<br>
“Both.” He grinned, still holding her hands.<br>
<br>
“They weren’t you. Your brother was trying to trick me, but I knew they weren’t you. I had to get rid of them.” Bunny held the expression on her face still, absorbing the explanation. “As for the second part, I knew that if I didn’t take you away from them that we could never be together. Ford is a bad person Bunny, he couldn’t accept that we belong together. But, it’s all taken care of now.” He lifted a hand and swept a stray strand of hair behind her ear. She furrowed her brow.<br>
<br>
“You didn’t do anything to Ford did you?” She asked, clearly concerned. He frowned at her and got out of his seat.<br>
<br>
“I didn’t kill him if that’s what you mean.”<br>
<br>
“What did you do?” She asked, a little more anger to her voice, she raised from her chair as well. If she was going to die, she may as well go down fighting. Feagins spun around, surprised by Bunny’s outburst. Anger reflected in his eyes, but he quickly pushed the emotion down and stepped close to her, placing a hand on her waist. He leaned down and spoke directly into her ear.<br>
<br>
“He’ll live. But if you continue to take his side over mine, I can’t guarantee for how long.” Bunny shuddered involuntarily. Risking her own life was one thing, after all, she reasoned, this guy was probably going to kill her anyway. But risking Ford’s life was quite another. Feagins noticed her response and nodded once. “We’ve come to an understanding then?” He asked, though it came out as more of a statement than a question. Bunny closed her eyes, fighting down her rapid pulse and urge to scream at the top of her lungs. She opened them again, seeing Feagins’s hazel eyes staring into her own. She nodded.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
“Grissom,” he answered the phone in his office, cradling it between his ear and shoulder as he sorted through paperwork on his desk.<br>
<br>
“Hey, it’s Adrian. Bouchard had some people go through Feagins’s apartment.” Grissom frowned.<br>
<br>
“That doesn’t sound entirely legal,” Grissom responded in a half sarcastic tone. He could have sworn he heard Adrian snicker on the other end.<br>
<br>
“You’d be surprised how quickly you can get a warrant when every person in government owes you,” he replied. Grissom pursed his lips and went back to the original topic.<br>
<br>
“What did they find?”<br>
<br>
“Well, he was definitely stalking her.”<br>
<br>
“We already figured that.”<br>
<br>
“Yeah, but the guys who went through the apartment said it looked like he may have been hired,” Adrian added. Grissom furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“Hired to stalk her?” Adrian shook his head.<br>
<br>
“Don’t know about that, but hired to take pictures of her. There are records indicating that he did some freelance PI work in his off time, and all of the pics decorating his walls correspond to dates and negatives in a certain file.” Grissom ran his hand through his hair.<br>
<br>
“So why stalk her then? Why start killing innocent women?” Grissom thought aloud.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know,” Adrian admitted. “I think he’s probably the only one who can tell you that.” Grissom sighed.<br>
<br>
“And maybe not even him.”<br>
<br>
“Yeah. Listen, he only used the client’s initials on the file, no full or partial name on anything.”<br>
<br>
“What were the initials?”<br>
<br>
“B.A.” Grissom scribbled the initials down on a scratch piece of paper. “They’re trying to connect the initials to any of his known friends or associates. Anything new over there?” Grissom rubbed his temple with his free hand.<br>
<br>
“We have people going door to door at every hotel and motel in the area. No one registered under his name though when we made the calls.” Adrian nodded, he had expected as much.<br>
<br>
“Let me know if you find out anything else.”<br>
<br>
“Yeah.” Grissom hung up the phone without a good-bye, as in his line of work it wasn’t customary. This latest development was beginning to gnaw at his gut instincts. He didn’t understand why, at least not yet.<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
Bunny had a glass of water about an hour ago, and had quickly passed out due to the drug that Feagins had slipped in it. She woke up with her right arm handcuffed to the headboard of the bed, and her senses dulled. She couldn’t tell whether she was just having a bad dream or it was real. Her vision was almost completely blurred and her sense of touch was practically numb. As the drug started to wear off, she felt someone on top of her, inside her. She panicked and started to flail around, kicking her legs, and trying to buck him off. Feagins, at almost twice her size, and quite a bit of it muscle, was able to keep her moderately controlled though, and soon finished. As he lay down on her, only propped up by one arm, he stared directly into her eyes.<br>
<br>
“You’re mine now.” He leaned in and whispered into her ear in a threatening tone. “Don’t forget it.” He rolls off the bed and goes to take a shower, knowing that she won’t be able to go anywhere. Bunny, still tired from the effects of the drug, but gaining more coherence by the moment, covered herself loosely with a sheet on the bed. She quickly scanned the room for a phone. There was one on the nightstand on her left side. She wouldn’t be able to reach it with her arm, and hadn’t discounted the possibility that Feagins had unplugged it.<br>
<br>
She maneuvered her body so her legs were facing that side of the bed, but it put quite a strain on her arm, and she winced when the handcuff cut into her small wrist. She was able to knock the receiver off the hook and heard the dial tone. ‘Thank you God.’ It was too far away for her to pick up the phone or the receiver, but she was barely able to hit the ‘0’ key with her toe. The shower was still running.<br>
<br>
“Front desk, how can I help you?” Bunny heard from the receiver on the end table. She couldn’t hear the person very well, so she presumed they wouldn’t be able to hear her well either.<br>
<br>
“I need you to call the police,” she said. She didn’t want to talk too loud, afraid that Feagins would hear her. Luckily, the person on the other end had good hearing.<br>
<br>
“What’s the problem?”<br>
<br>
“I’m being held hostage. I don’t know what room I’m in, but I need help. Please help me.” She could feel the tears forming in her eyes, and her voice was becoming a little choked up. The woman on the other end of the phone nodded, hearing the fear in her voice. She had seen enough stuff in Las Vegas to make her believe someone when they said they were in trouble.<br>
<br>
“Okay sweetie. I’ll call them right now.” She hung up the phone. The shower turned off and Bunny’s heart skipped a beat. She realized that there was no way she would be able to get the receiver back on the phone and that when Feagins saw it that she would be facing her death even sooner. She frantically tried to kick the phone off the table altogether, hoping that he would think that she tried to get the phone but was unable to. It worked, and the phone crashed to the floor. The bathroom door opened and he peered out to see what the noise had been. He saw the phone on the floor, making a beeping noise, and cocked his eyebrow at her. She looked uncomfortable and scared. He sighed, and came to sit next to her, only wearing a towel around his waist.<br>
<br>
“Sweetheart,” he paused. “Why can’t you just accept that we’re together now?” He looked over at her, and noticed that her wrist was bleeding badly. Besides looking scared, she was also looking pale. He murmured some profanities and reached out to inspect her arm closer. She tried to pull it away from him, but was unsuccessful, and only made the handcuff rip into her skin a little more. She winced and finally let the water from her eyes start to run down her face.<br>
